						               													<description>This &amp;quot;Krieg-Kit&amp;quot; conflict game was designed and published by Marty Silva in 1973. The game deals with the both the  strategic and tactical aspects of the Peloponnesian War.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are two large monochrome (light and dark blue/black)map parts that depict Ancient Greece in 480. There is also a small 8 page rulebook, a battle results table and a counter sheet with adhesive printed counters that must be cut and peeled. There are a 138 counters, both men and ships. Basically, the game is a very early homemade DTP effort (long before the term was invented)from Orland Park, Illinois.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Fairly rare in wargaming circles, yet a simple and quick simulation of one of history's great wars.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
